The BRTs were also very good at predicting the observed extent of rainfed rice (Pearson's r = 0.87 between observed and modelled extent; Fig. S3, Appendix A). The extent of rainfed rice was predicted to be high in 2408 cells and low in 5566 cells (AUC = 0.89, sensitivity = 84%, specificity = 79%, based on a threshold extent of 1517.93 ha; 
 Fig. 2b). Comparing CEM and BRT outputs showed that 73% (5819/7974) of cells were in agreement (
 Fig. 2c), such that 55% of CEM rainfed rice presences were predicted by BRTs to have high extent of rice, and 80% of CEM absences were predicted to have low extent.
